  <h2 class="vc-feat-h reveal">About giving to <em>E5 Enclave.</em></h2>
  <article class="vc-prose reveal" style="max-width:780px; margin:0 auto;">

<h3>Is my donation tax-deductible?</h3>
<p>E5 Enclave Incorporated is a recognized 501(c)(3) public charitable organization (EIN: 99-3822441). Donations are generally tax-deductible to the extent permitted by law. We issue tax receipts for every contribution. Consult your tax advisor for guidance specific to your situation.</p>

<h3>Where are E5 Enclave's financials published?</h3>
<p>E5 Enclave files Form 990 annually with the IRS. Our commitment is to publish summary financials openly — on this site and in the annual report. The operating doctrine: <em>what is measured cannot be dismissed.</em> That applies to our own books as much as to any dataset we produce.</p>

<h3>Can I designate my gift to a specific program?</h3>
<p>Yes. In the checkout notes field, designate your gift to McCartney Academy, Lineage Farms · FarmBlock, Block to the Boardroom, or The Record (research and publication). Undesignated gifts go to the area of greatest need as determined by the Council.</p>

<h3>How does monthly giving work?</h3>
<p>Monthly donors are the backbone of a publication of record. Select "Monthly" above. Your card is charged on the same date each month. You can pause or cancel at any time — no penalty, no questions. Monthly donors receive our annual report and program updates by email.</p>

<h3>Is there another way to give?</h3>
<p>Stock, DAF (donor-advised fund), wire, and institutional gift inquiries: write <a href="mailto:contact@e5enclave.com">contact@e5enclave.com</a> with "Gift" in the subject line. We respond within two business days.</p>

  </article>
